tead of rescheduling of crop loans, farmers who are severely affected by natural calamities will now get 2% interest subvention and additional 3% interest subsidy on timely repayment.PM Kisan Samman Nidhi YojanaHow To Check Name in PM Kisan Samman Nidhi Yojana 2020 Beneficiary ListAll the applicant farmers can download the complete list of PM Kisan Samman Nidhi Yojana 2020 beneficiaries through the link given below:- PM Kisan Samman Nidhi Yojana List of BeneficiariesAll those farmers whose name appears in the PM KISAN 2020 Beneficiary List will get financial assistance of Rs. 6,000 p.a through DBT Mode.How to Fill PM KISAN Samman Nidhi Yojana Online Application Form / Track StatusPM Kisan Samman Nidhi Yojana Form will remain available at the official website pmkisan.nic.in. The PM Kisan Yojana online application form will appear as follows:-PM Kisan Samman Nidhi FormHere candidates can enter their details and click at the \u201cSubmit\u201d button to apply online for PM Kisan Samman Nidhi Yojana 2020. Check the complete process to apply online and track PM Kisan application status here \u2013 PM KISAN Samman Nidhi Yojana Apply Online / Status Process.Know How to Make Offline Registration for PM Kisan Samman Nidhi Yojana 2020To learn the complete offline application process for PM Kisan Samman Nidhi Yojana at common service centers, click the link below:- PM Kisan Samman Nidhi Yojana Registration 2020 at CSCsPM KISAN Scheme 2020 Combined BenefitsThis income support scheme or Modi Rythu Bandhu Scheme 2019 is based on the lines of Telangana\u2019s Rythu Bandhu Scheme (Rs. 8,000 per annum) and Odisha\u2019s Kalia Scheme (Rs. 10,000 per annum). Both these schemes have achieved immediate success previously. Now these schemes will provide additional (combined) benefits to farmers which are described below:-Now in Telangana, farmers will get Rs. 14,000 per year as combination of Rythu Bandhu (8000 p.a) + PM Kisan Scheme (Rs. 6000 p.a).Accordingly, farmers in Odisha would get Rs. 16,000 per year as combination of Kalia Yojana (Rs. 10000 p.a) + PM-KISAN Scheme (Rs. 6000 p.a).Similarly in Jharkhand, farmers would get combined benefit of Rs. 11000 p.a as a combination of Krishi Ashirwad Yojana (Rs. 5000 p.a for Kharif crops) + PM KISAN Scheme (Rs. 6000 p.a)Now the central govt. will provide 2% rebate on loans taken from Kisan Credit Card. Moreover, all those farmers who pays their installments on time will get another rebate of 3% on KCC loans.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}